us collaboration: Business survival after partners shut down or form new partnerships', Strategic Management Journal, 17: 99-115. Stahl, G. K. and Voigt, A. (2004) 'Meta-analyses of the performance implications of the cultural difference in mergers and acquisitions', Academy of Management Proceedings, 12(6): 11-16.Tsang, Eric W.K. and Yip, Paul S.L. (2007) 'Economic distance and the survival of foreign direct investments', Academy of Management Journal, 50(5): 1156-68.Tushman, M. & Romanelli, E. (1985) 'Organizational evolution: A metamorphosis model of convergence and reorientation', research in organizational behavior, 7: 171-222. United Nations Conference on Trade and Development 2008. World Investment Report 2008:  Transnational Corporations and the Infrastructure Challenge. New York and Geneva: United Nations. Vermuelen, F. & Barkema, H. (2001) 'Learning through acquisitions', Academy of Management Journal, 44(3): 457-76. Very, P., Lubatkin, M., & Caroli, R. (1996) 'A cross-national assessment of acculturative stress in recent European mergers', International Studies of Management and Organization, 26(1): 59-86. Watson, D.G. (2007) 'Acquisitions: How to avoid implementation pitfalls and improve the odds of success', Global Business and Organizational Excellence, 27(1): 7-19. Weber, Y. (1996) 'Corporate cultural fit and performance in mergers and acquisitions', Human Relations, 49(9): 1181-201. Wu, S. (2008) 'Bank Mergers and Acquisitions- an Evaluation of the ‘four pillars’ policy in Australia', Australian Economic Papers, 47(2): 141-55. Xu, D. & Lu, J.W. (2007) 'Technological knowledge, product relatedness, and parent control: The effect on ijv survival', Journal of Business Research, 60(11): 1166-79. Zollo, M. & Singh, H. (2004) 'Deliberate learning in corporate acquisitions: Post-acquisition strategies and integration capability in U.S. Bank mergers', Strategic Management Journal, 25(13): 1233-56.Zollo, M. & Winter, S.G. (2002) ‘Deliberate Learni