口試委員-李光中



關鍵字(中)
文化景觀林業文化景觀阿裡山


關鍵字(英)
Cultural LandscapeForestry Cultural LandscapeAlishan


學科別分類



中文摘要
台灣過去習慣以單一定點來看待古蹟，本研究試圖融入文化景觀的新觀念，以整個林業軸帶來思考。「文化景觀」指的是人類與自然互動之結果，而「林業文化景觀」是指人類透過他們的生活方式，為了滿足以及改善需求，而利用、取用森林自然資源，進而改變、演育而成之景觀面貌。這包含了林業「所衍生的實質具體層面」以及「精神層面的歷史文化意義」兩個面向持續性演化展現之情形。 本研究經由文獻回顧整理出，要達到符合作為文化資產的林業文化景觀，必須先針對其基本內涵條件加以分析，找出構成林業文化景觀之獨特性因子，包括人類活動、自然條件、有形元素和無形元素等實質內涵判別，歸納出關鍵之重要影響林業文化景觀因子以及其他一般影響因子。最後進行全面性的檢視與評估林業文化景觀之完整性與真實性面向。經過上述的流程分析與檢視，以達到符合作為文化資產之林業文化景觀。此外，檢視與評估後的林業文化景觀應能與全國性、同質性的林業文化景觀相互評比分析，找出具代表性、時代性及罕見性之重要依準，才能夠達到登錄法定的標準。本論文並將以阿裡山地區作為林業文化景觀主題的探討區域。 阿裡山地區由於林業產業歷史發展脈絡，經由人於森林中與自然環境產生互動所顯示形塑出明確與土地開墾互動之情形與景觀上的變化，且至今仍然持續性演化中，並留下歷史性的證物，包含有形與無形文化資產的存留與其中展現出的精神歷史文化意義。阿裡山林業文化景觀之各項因子同時具代表性、時代性與罕見性等特質，具台灣的林業發展有重大意義與價值，因此，本論文最後提出阿裡山地區仍然具有作為文化資產林業文化景觀之價值與潛力。


英文摘要
In the past Taiwan, is to look at a single point as monuments, this study attempted to integrate into the new concept of cultural landscape in order to bring the entire axis of forestry thinking, "cultural landscapes" refers the result of the interaction of the human beings and nature. And "Cultural landscape forestry" refers to human beings, through their ways of life, in order to meet their needs to improve to make use of, and to access to natural resources, forests, and to change the face of the landscape. This includes the forestry, "derived from the specific level in real terms" and "the spirit of the historical and cultural significance levels" for the continuing evolution of two of the cases show. According to the literature review in this research, the forestry culture landscape, to be qualified to be listed, firstly be first analyzed the basic condition to find out the unique factor to become an forestry culture landscape. The factor includes human activities, nature conditions, tangible & invisible elements. Then the critical factor should be concluding that had more impact on forestry culture landscape. At last, an overall review must he made to evaluate the integrity and authenticity of forestry culture landscape. The forestry will be more qualified to be listed through the above procedure of analyzing and evaluating. Moreover, it’ll be better to compare with similar culture landscape nationally, and find out the important specification that is representing, epoch and rare, and then, it’ll be more fitting to the standard to be listed. Alishan area is to be explored as the main theme of the thesis. Alishan area, because of bringing in of forestry industry has, developed a specific interact of land cultivation and sight changes through the interact between human and natural environment. Until now the evolution is still continuing and leaves historical witnesses, including tangible and intangible cultural assets and shows spiritual and historical culture effect, at the same time it is representing, epoch and rare that create significance and value for Taiwan forests. Therefore, The Alishan area is still considered with great value to be listed in the forestry culture landscape.


